<TITLE> Abahani invited to AFC President's Cup </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 7 (bdnews24.com)  B. League champions Abahani Limited was invited to play the AFC (Asian Football Confederation) President's Cup, said a Bangladesh Football Federation (BFF) official. The national league champions are generally allowed to play the AFC President's Cup and the AFC asked Bangladesh to send their entries last month. The BFF found them in difficulty for not having the national league champions and sought a clarification from the AFC whether B. league champions would be allowed to play the tournament. The AFC Monday confirmed the BFF that Abahani would be eligible to play the President's Cup. The qualification round will start on March 20, but the venues are yet to be decided. Apart from Bangladesh, the national league champions from Bhutan, Cambodia, Chinese Taipei, Kyrgyzstan, Myanmar, Nepal, Pakistan, Sri Lanka, Tajikistan and Turkmenistan were also invited by the football governing body of Asia. 
